# Security Boundaries

- Runtime financial state belongs under external `DATA_ROOT` / `FFOS_DATA_ROOT`, never in git.
- Keep personal and QA/demo environments separate (`APP_ENV`, distinct data roots, synthetic-only QA).
- Do not bind the app to `0.0.0.0` or add external data transmission without explicit owner approval.
- Preserve append-only audit behavior for financial decisions and settings changes.
- New dependencies need license compatibility (MPL-2.0) and a quick supply-chain review.
- CI and repo checks must stay synthetic-only and must not weaken secret or sensitive-artifact scans.
